Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

Hi Mike,

Looks great, thanks for working on this!

I have couple of concerns 'though. First of all even this comes via bug report, I think this is functionality enhancement enough that probably we would need FFE or postpone this to Kilo. What others think?

The other concern for me is that we're trying to retire v1 api and it has been talked a lot to not try to bring new functionality to it. Would it make sense/be reasonably easy to make this only to v2 api?

Other than those and my inline comment to commit message, I'd be happy to see this landing. 

Welcome to the world of Glance!

Patch Set 4:

Hello Erno,
thank you for the comments.
My thoughts are as follows:
First, I think this is more an enhancement rather than a bug fix, so it can be postponed to Kilo. I hope consumers will cope with this :)
Second, there is a problem with python-glanceclient that currently works on v1 and doesn't support lots of v2 api. I add sort functionality to v2, but there is a lot of stuff to work on. It means users will have to switch to v2 explicitly with --os-image-api-version if they want to use this ability.
So, I suggest two options:
1. Add this code as-is to both v1/v2. I don't think it's a big deal, because backward compatibility is not broken.
2. Add only v2 part, but then we'll have to switch python-glancecilent to v2 too, in other words to implement full v2 api there and make it default.
I would be glad if glance developers (especially core-team members) expressed their opinions on the matter.

World of Glance seems nice. I hope I like it :)
